text: Michael J. O'Connor (December 15, 1928 â€“ October 24, 2018) was an American politician. He was born in Sioux Falls, South Dakota. He was a member of the South Dakota House of Representatives and South Dakota State Senate. He was President Pro Tempore of the Senate from 1975 to 1976. He was a member of the Democratic Party. O'Connor died in Sioux Falls from skin cancer on October 24, 2018 at the age of 89. ==References== Category:1928 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Deaths from skin cancer Category:State legislators of the United States Category:Politicians from South Dakota Category:People from Sioux Falls, South Dakota Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:Cancer deaths in South Dakota
